OL,3,CReeves urged to reverse 'rash' tax
OL,4,Ccommitments and reform system by think
OL,5,Ctank
OL,7,FRachel Reeves should "reject the path
OL,8,Fof least resistance" and consider
OL,9,Frowing back on her "rash" tax
OL,10,Fcommitments at the Budget, a leading
OL,11,Fthink tank has said.
OL,13,FThe Institute for Government (IfG)
OL,14,Fsaid Labour's "unrealistic" approach
OL,15,Fto tax has left the Chancellor
OL,16,Freaching for "piecemeal changes".
OL,18,FThe Government has repeatedly said it
OL,19,Fwill not increase the rates of VAT,
OL,20,Fincome tax or national insurance at
OL,21,Fthe Budget in November.
