OL,3,CReeves urged to reverse 'rash' tax
OL,4,Ccommitments and reform system by think
OL,5,Ctank
OL,7,FIfG deputy economist Tom Pope said:
OL,8,F"This autumn, the Chancellor finds
OL,9,Fherself in a difficult position.
OL,11,F"With tax rises all but inevitable,
OL,12,Fshe should reject the path of least
OL,13,Fresistance, often taken by her
OL,14,Fpredecessors, of raising taxes in an
OL,15,Finconsistent way based on what seems
OL,16,Feasiest.
OL,18,F"Instead, now is the time to commit to
OL,19,Ftax reform and lay out an agenda on
OL,20,Ftax that fits with her broader growth
OL,21,Fobjectives."
